<li id="cite_note-53"><b><a href="#cite_ref-53" title="">^</a></b> Meltzoff, A.N., &amp; Decety, J. (2003). What imitation tells us about social cognition: A rapprochement between developmental psychology and cognitive neuroscience. The Philosophical Transactions of the Royal Society, London, 358, 491-500.</li>
<li id="cite_note-54"><b><a href="#cite_ref-54" title="">^</a></b> Sommerville, J. A., &amp; Decety, J. (2006). Weaving the fabric of social interaction: Articulating developmental psychology and cognitive neuroscience in the domain of motor cognition. Psychonomic Bulletin &amp; Review, 13, 179-200.</li>
<li id="cite_note-55"><b><a href="#cite_ref-55" title="">^</a></b> Keysers C and Gazzola V(2007) <i>Integrating simulation and theory of mind: from self to social cognition</i>. Trends in Cognitive Sciences 11(5):194-6<a href="http://www.bcn-nic.nl/txt/people/publications/TICS_Sim_Tom.pdf" class="external autonumber" title="http://www.bcn-nic.nl/txt/people/publications/TICS_Sim_Tom.pdf" rel="nofollow">[10]</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-56"><b><a href="#cite_ref-56" title="">^</a></b> Cheng, Y., Tzeng, O.J., Decety, J., &amp; Hsieh, J.C. (2006). Gender differences in the human mirror system: a magnetoencephalography study. NeuroReport, 17, 1115-1119.</li>
